<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="228" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.55/29.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Chinese Legation informs Department that suspension for sixty days of
                            prohibition against Chinese immigration into Cuba will expire end of
                            May.</p>
                        <pb facs="0390" n="274" xml:id="pg_274"/>
                        <p>You are instructed to cooperate with Chinese Chargé d’Affaires in an
                            effort to induce Cuban Government to allow the suspending order to
                            remain in force pending conclusion of treaty between China and Cuba.</p>
                        <p>Report by telegraph.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>